<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-09T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-09T15:00:00-05:00" n="707" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d707">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/2715: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Drew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-09T15:00:00-05:00">October 9, 1933—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>73. Your 108, October 5, 8 p.m. You are authorized to include in the
                            proposed exchange of notes a provision along the lines of paragraph 2 of
                            your telegram No. 106 of September 28, noon.</p>
                        <p>Was the exchange of notes authorized in the Department’s telegram No. 26
                            of April 3 [<hi rend="italic">13</hi>], 1 p.m. effected?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>